macOS-style vector frame for the dock, with live settings for "Tahoe Blur".

Draw an optional rounded outline over the dock with a QML Rectangle (no image).
Its corner radius defaults to the blur radius, so the outline follows KWin's
native blur region by construction and scales with the dock (icon count / zoom).

The frame is opt-in per skin via all-optional Config.qml properties, so existing
skins are unaffected:
  frame        : bool   -- draw the outline
  frameColor   : color  -- outline color (default #59ffffff)
  frameFill    : color  -- interior tint over the blur (default transparent)
  frameBorder  : int    -- outline width in px (default 1)
  frameRadius  : int    -- corner radius (default = blurRadius)
  blurInset    : int    -- shrink the blur region inwards (default 0)

blurInset pulls the blur region in and lowers its radius by the same amount, so
it stays concentric with the frame; KWin's blur has a soft edge that bleeds a
few px past the mask, and the inset keeps that edge under the frame outline.

For the "Tahoe Blur" skin the corner radius, the panel tint (its brightness) and
the blur inset are exposed in the plasmoid settings and applied live:
  * config/main.xml      : tahoeFrameRadius / tahoeTintStrength / tahoeTintDark /
                           tahoeBlurInset.
  * ConfigAppearance.qml  : radius + tint + inset sliders and a dark-tint
                            checkbox, shown only when "Tahoe Blur" is selected.
  * main.qml              : loadSkinConfig() overrides blurRadius/frameRadius/
                            frameFill/blurInset from those keys for that skin; the
                            config signals re-run loadSkinConfig(); the blur region
                            is re-applied on radius/inset changes so it updates live.
